&lt;p&gt;The Children’s Emergency Department is open 24 hrs a day and sees on average 90 - 100 children a day. The department is dynamic and progressive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to Covid-19 and the relocation of our Children’s ED an opportunity has arisen to increase our staffing establishment for band 5 staff nurses to extend their development in a Children’s environment working alongside Children’s nurses, Consultants, ENPs and GPs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person must like a challenge, respond well to the demands of a busy department and enjoy working at a fast pace in a multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department encourages and supports professional development including extended nursing skills, study modules at university and in-house study days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
